name: Should You Always Press The Handbrake Button?
description:
Should you always push the handbrake button? People say donâ€™t yank the hand brake without pushing the button. Letâ€™s pull back the covers on this  myth. When you pull up on the hand brake, this pulls on a cable. This cable forces pressure to be applied to the rear brake pads, locking the wheel. The hand brake uses a ratcheting mechanism, so as you pull it up, the pawl clicks along the gear teeth until you stop pulling, where itâ€™s held in pace by the nearest gear tooth. The button is simply there to release the pawl away from the gear, so you can disengage the parking brake. So itâ€™s two robust metal parts, with very little speed between them, and thus negligible friction and wear generated. But to be safe, I stopped using my car entirely and now just walk, so that my parking brake doesnâ€™t wear out.
